directly applicable in agriculture, as we study crop-associated nitrogen fixers, but the ideas are more general.</gtr:exploitationPathways><gtr:id>91C2462C-AF54-44F1-BC3B-01874B1437CE</gtr:id><gtr:sectors><gtr:sector>Agriculture, Food and Drink,Education,Environment,Healthcare</gtr:sector></gtr:sectors></gtr:keyFindingsOutput><gtr:otherResearchOutputs/><gtr:policyInfluenceOutputs/><gtr:productOutputs/><gtr:researchDatabaseAndModelOutputs/><gtr:researchMaterialOutputs/><gtr:softwareAndTechnicalProductOutputs/><gtr:spinOutOutputs/></gtr:output><gtr:publications><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/193F93C0-4B61-4F4F-A531-8972AE78BC56"><gtr:id>193F93C0-4B61-4F4F-A531-8972AE78BC56</gtr:id><gtr:title>Symbiosis within Symbiosis: Evolving Nitrogen-Fixing Legume Symbionts.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>Trends in microbiology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/20f48b2c9463c3756b6438fa9c8756f6"><gtr:id>20f48b2c9463c3756b6438fa9c8756f6</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Remigi P</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2016-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0966-842X</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/75CC488E-440D-41B1-8018-A0EAD22F17D2"><gtr:id>75CC488E-440D-41B1-8018-A0EAD22F17D2</gtr:id><gtr:title>Population mixing of Rhizobium leguminosarum bv. viciae nodulating Vicia faba: the role of recombination and lateral gene transfer.</gtr:title><gtr:parentPublicationTitle>FEMS microbiology ecology</gtr:parentPublicationTitle><gtr:authors><gtr:author url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/person/825efe6eb09877f632291dc68876d32e"><gtr:id>825efe6eb09877f632291dc68876d32e</gtr:id><gtr:otherNames>Tian CF</gtr:otherNames></gtr:author></gtr:authors><gtr:date>2010-01-01</gtr:date><gtr:issn>0168-6496</gtr:issn></gtr:publication><gtr:publication url="http://gtr.rcuk.ac.uk:80/publication/6999BD25-44BD-4DE1-A187-C024305EF40C"><gtr:id>6999BD25-44BD-4DE1-A187-C024305EF40C</